        5 guests<br>2 nights<br>$522.49 total<br>
        <span class="accom-code">HMD4S5984M</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="days-container">

    <!-- Jul 15 evening -->
    <div class="day-card">
      <div class="day-color-bar" style="background:#2E7D5E"></div>
      <div class="day-header">
        <div class="day-number">15</div>
        <div><div class="day-title">Arrive + Grand-Place Evening</div><div class="day-date">Wednesday, July 15 (evening)</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Evening</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Check In + Grand-Place</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">Drop bags at Rue Bara 159, Anderlecht (self check-in via lockbox, after 3:00 PM) then head to Grand-Place. Many argue this is the most beautiful town square in Europe. Gothic guild halls and the ornate City Hall surrounded by gold-trimmed facades. Stunning by day, transcendent at night when lit up. Walk it twice.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-landmark">Landmark</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Night</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Belgian Beer Bar Crawl — Grand-Place Area</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">Belgium has 1,500+ beers and you need to start drinking them immediately. Delirium Café near Grand-Place holds the Guinness World Record for most beers on a menu (2,000+). Nearby, À la Mort Subite ("Sudden Death") is a century-old Art Nouveau café serving gueuze straight from the cask. Order whatever the bartender recommends and keep going. Tonight is purely a drinking night.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-nightlife">Bar Crawl</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Jul 16 full day -->
    <div class="day-card">
      <div class="day-color-bar" style="background:#2E7D5E"></div>
      <div class="day-header">
        <div class="day-number">16</div>
        <div><div class="day-title">Full Day — Brussels</div><div class="day-date">Thursday, July 16</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Morning</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Manneken Pis + Comic Strip Murals Route</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">The famous bronze fountain — smaller than expected but a rite of passage. Then follow Brussels's Comic Strip Route: 50+ enormous street murals of Tintin, the Smurfs, Lucky Luke, and Marsupilami scattered across the city. The best way to discover neighborhoods.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-landmark">Landmark</span>
            <br>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1531316282941-5a77ef8985a5?w=800&q=80" crossorigin="anonymous" alt="Brussels street art comic murals" class="attraction-photo">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Midday</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Magritte Museum</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">The world's largest collection of René Magritte's surrealist work — the artist behind the man in the bowler hat. Even if you're not an art person, Magritte's paintings are genuinely strange, funny, and unforgettable.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-culture">Museum</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Lunch</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Belgian Frites — Maison Antoine</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">The legendary Brussels friterie near Place Jourdan. Thick-cut, double-fried in beef fat, served in a paper cone with mayonnaise. Belgian fries are categorically different from what you know. This is the pilgrimage spot.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-food">Food</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Afternoon</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">The Atomium</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">A giant steel atom structure built for the 1958 World's Fair — one of the most architecturally singular landmarks in Europe. Panoramic city views from the top sphere. Worth the 20-minute metro ride. Go at golden hour.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-landmark">Landmark</span>
            <br>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1491557345352-5929e343eb89?w=800&q=80" crossorigin="anonymous" alt="Atomium Brussels" class="attraction-photo">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Evening</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Waffles + Chocolate Shopping (Royal Galleries)</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">Brussels street waffles (gaufres) are eaten topped with cream and fruit — they're not what you get at brunch back home. Then hit the Galeries Royales Saint-Hubert for Neuhaus or Pierre Marcolini chocolate. Pick up gifts here.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-food">Food</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Night</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Cantillon Tap Room + Moeder Lambic</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">If you didn't make it to Cantillon during the day, Moeder Lambic Fontainas is the best bar in Brussels to drink serious Belgian beer — 40+ taps, all Belgian, all outstanding. Order a kriek (cherry lambic), a Rochefort 10, and whatever seasonal they have. You're in the world capital of beer. Drink accordingly.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-nightlife">Drinks</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Jul 17 depart -->
    <div class="day-card">
      <div class="day-color-bar" style="background:#2E7D5E"></div>
      <div class="day-header">
        <div class="day-number">17</div>
        <div><div class="day-title">Morning + Train to Amsterdam</div><div class="day-date">Friday, July 17</div></div>
        <span class="day-badge badge-free">🚄 Brussels → Amsterdam</span>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Morning</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">⏰ Checkout by 11:00 AM — then Cantillon Brewery (if time allows)</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">The only active lambic brewery in Brussels — a 1900s time capsule of wooden barrels and wild-yeast fermentation. Included in "1,000 Places to See Before You Die." Check hours before you go.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-culture">Culture</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Midday</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Train to Amsterdam Zuid (Omio · DFNPJXC)</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">Brussels-Midi → Amsterdam Zuid. Friday July 17 — exact departure time in your Omio app. ~1h 50m. Note: Amsterdam Zuid is a quick metro ride from city center (not Amsterdam Centraal).</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-free">Transit</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
  <div class="must-eat">
    <div class="must-eat-label">Must Eat in Brussels</div>
    <div class="pill-row">
      <span class="pill">Belgian frites + mayo (Maison Antoine)</span><span class="pill">Brussels waffle</span>
      <span class="pill">Moules-frites</span><span class="pill">Pierre Marcolini chocolate</span><span class="pill">Speculoos</span>
    </div>
    <div class="must-eat-label" style="margin-top:0.75rem">Signature Drinks</div>
    <div class="pill-row">
      <span class="pill" style="border-color:#2E7D5E;color:#2E7D5E">🍺 Trappist ale — Chimay, Orval, or Rochefort; order at any traditional estaminet</span>
      <span class="pill" style="border-color:#2E7D5E;color:#2E7D5E">🍺 Gueuze — Brussels's wild-fermented lambic blend; dry, funky, unlike anything else</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ AMSTERDAM ============ -->
<section class="city-section alt" id="amsterdam">
  <div class="city-header">
    <div>
      <div class="city-eyebrow c-amsterdam">Stop 04 · Netherlands</div>
      <h2 class="city-name c-amsterdam">Amsterdam</h2>
      <div class="city-meta">
        <span>July 17–19</span><span class="city-sep">·</span>
        <span>2 nights</span><span class="city-sep">·</span>
        <span>Canals, Van Gogh & the Golden Age</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <span class="city-tag" style="background:#7B3FA0">Netherlands</span>
  </div>

  <div class="city-photo">
    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1534351590666-13e3e96b5017?w=1200&q=80" crossorigin="anonymous" alt="Amsterdam canal houses at sunset">
    <div class="city-photo-caption">Amsterdam's UNESCO canal ring at golden hour</div>
  </div>

  <div class="accom-banner">
    <div class="accom-card">
      <div class="accom-icon">🏠</div>
      <div>
        <div class="accom-label">Airbnb · Amsterdam</div>
        <div class="accom-name">The Amsterdam arch suite Central spacious</div>
        <div class="accom-address">1012 DV Amsterdam, Netherlands — City Center · Host: Diana</div>
        <div class="accom-times">
          <div class="accom-time-block">
            <div class="accom-time-label">Check-in</div>
            <div class="accom-time-val">Fri, Jul 17</div>
            <div class="accom-time-sub">After 4:00 PM</div>
          </div>
          <div class="accom-time-block">
            <div class="accom-time-label">Checkout</div>
            <div class="accom-time-val">Sun, Jul 19</div>
            <div class="accom-time-sub">By 10:00 AM</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accom-meta">
        5 guests<br>2 nights<br>$1,587.51 total<br>
        <span class="accom-code">HMQDENDBFH</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="days-container">

    <!-- Jul 17 evening -->
    <div class="day-card">
      <div class="day-color-bar" style="background:#7B3FA0"></div>
      <div class="day-header">
        <div class="day-number">17</div>
        <div><div class="day-title">Arrive + Jordaan Evening</div><div class="day-date">Friday, July 17 (evening)</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Arrival</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Check In + Rent Bikes Immediately</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">Check into the arch suite at 1012 DV Amsterdam City Center (after 4:00 PM, host Diana) then rent bikes immediately. Amsterdam was designed for bikes. Renting one in the first hour changes the entire trip — everything is faster, more fun, and more local. MacBike and Starbikes are reliable near Centraal station.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-culture">Local Pro Tip</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Evening</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Jordaan Neighborhood + Canal Walk</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">The most photogenic neighborhood in Amsterdam — 17th-century canal houses, independent galleries, and cozy brown cafés. Prinsengracht and Keizersgracht at dusk are as beautiful as anywhere in Europe.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-landmark">Neighborhood</span>
            <br>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583069955278-87f02e4a0db2?w=800&q=80" crossorigin="anonymous" alt="Jordaan Amsterdam canal" class="attraction-photo">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Night</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Brown Café Crawl — Jordaan</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">Amsterdam's brown cafés are the best bars in Europe — dark wood, candles, Heineken on tap, Jenever shots, zero pretension. Start at Café 't Smalle (1786, one of the oldest), then Café de Vergulde Gaper, then wherever the night takes you. Order a kopstootje — a Jenever with a beer chaser — and do it like the Dutch. Tonight is for getting properly acquainted with Amsterdam.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-nightlife">Bar Crawl</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Jul 18 full day -->
    <div class="day-card">
      <div class="day-color-bar" style="background:#7B3FA0"></div>
      <div class="day-header">
        <div class="day-number">18</div>
        <div><div class="day-title">Museums, Canal Cruise & De Wallen</div><div class="day-date">Saturday, July 18</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Morning</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Van Gogh Museum</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">The world's largest Van Gogh collection — 200+ paintings tracing his entire career from the dark Dutch period to the explosive color of Arles and Saint-Rémy. The Sunflowers, The Bedroom, and dozens of self-portraits. Book tickets weeks in advance in summer — it sells out.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-culture">Museum</span>
            <br>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1575505586569-646b2ca898fc?w=800&q=80" crossorigin="anonymous" alt="Van Gogh Museum Amsterdam" class="attraction-photo">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Late Morn.</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Rijksmuseum</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">One of the truly great art museums in the world — Rembrandt's Night Watch, Vermeer's The Milkmaid, and the full sweep of Dutch Golden Age painting and craftsmanship. The building itself is extraordinary. If you see two museums this trip, make it these two.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-culture">Museum</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Afternoon</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Canal Cruise</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">The single best way to experience Amsterdam. A 1-hour boat tour through the UNESCO World Heritage canal ring — 60 miles of canals, 1,500 bridges. The perspective from water level is completely different. Evening cruises are especially atmospheric.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-landmark">Experience</span>
            <br>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1576924542622-772281b13f82?w=800&q=80" crossorigin="anonymous" alt="Amsterdam canal boat cruise" class="attraction-photo">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Late Aft.</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">De Wallen (Red Light District)</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">Worth walking through for the architecture and history alone. Medieval buildings, hidden courtyards (seek out the Begijnhof — a tranquil secret garden from the 14th century), and some of the city's oldest churches sit right next to it all.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-culture">Neighborhood</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Evening</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Heineken Experience (Optional)</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">The brewery tour is touristy but genuinely entertaining — beer history, science, and three complimentary beers on the rooftop terrace. Good group fun.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-culture">Culture</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Late Night</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Leidseplein & Rembrandtplein Bar Crawl</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">Amsterdam's two main nightlife squares. Leidseplein has the big outdoor terraces and live music bars — Paradiso (legendary music venue) is right there. Rembrandtplein is louder and more chaotic, ringed by packed bars. Last night in Europe: make it count. The trams run all night so getting back is easy no matter how deep you go.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-nightlife">Last Night Out</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Jul 19 departure -->
    <div class="day-card">
      <div class="day-color-bar" style="background:#7B3FA0"></div>
      <div class="day-header">
        <div class="day-number">19</div>
        <div><div class="day-title">Last Morning + Fly Home</div><div class="day-date">Sunday, July 19 · BA431 departs 11:35</div></div>
        <span class="day-badge badge-free">✈ AMS → LHR → JFK</span>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">Early</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">⏰ Checkout by 10:00 AM — then Albert Cuypmarkt (if time allows)</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">Amsterdam's biggest street market — fresh stroopwafels, Dutch aged cheese, herring sandwiches, and flowers. A great last-morning experience before the airport.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-food">Market</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-time">~9:00</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-name">Head to Amsterdam Schiphol (AMS)</div>
            <div class="timeline-desc">BA431 departs AMS 11:35 → London Heathrow (LHR T5) 11:55. Connection 1h 25m. Then BA177 departs LHR 13:20 → JFK Terminal 8, arriving 16:15. Total ~9h 15m home.</div>
            <span class="timeline-type type-free">Transit</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
  <div class="must-eat">
    <div class="must-eat-label">Must Eat in Amsterdam</div>
    <div class="pill-row">
      <span class="pill">Stroopwafel (fresh, from market)</span><span class="pill">Haring (raw herring)</span><span class="pill">Aged Gouda</span>
      <span class="pill">Bitterballen</span><span class="pill">Rijsttafel (Indonesian feast)</span><span class="pill">Poffertjes</span>
    </div>
    <div class="must-eat-label" style="margin-top:0.75rem">Signature Drinks</div>
    <div class="pill-row">
      <span class="pill" style="border-color:#7B3FA0;color:#7B3FA0">🍸 Jenever — Dutch gin, served neat in a tulip glass; the original gin</span>
      <span class="pill" style="border-color:#7B3FA0;color:#7B3FA0">🍺 Heineken on tap — non-negotiable; tastes better here than anywhere else</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FOOTER -->
<footer>
  <div style="margin-bottom:0.4rem"><strong>Let the Fun Begin · Summer 2026</strong></div>
  <div>Bologna · Paris · Brussels · Amsterdam · July 10–19, 2026</div>
</footer>

<script>
  const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.city-section');
  const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('nav a');
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      if (entry.isIntersecting) {
        const id = entry.target.id;
        navLinks.forEach(link => {
          link.classList.toggle('active', link.getAttribute('href') === '#' + id);
        });
      }
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.25 });
  sections.forEach(s => observer.observe(s));
</script>
</body>
</html>
